
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconName 0

class Employee {
  - name: String
  - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class Planner extends Employee {
  - username: String
  - password: String
}

class AdministrativeStaff extends Employee {
  - fieldOfActivity: String
  - username: String
  - password: String
}

class Driver extends Employee {
  - assignedOrders: List<Order>
}

class Customer {
  - name: String
  - billingAddress: String
}

class PartnerCompany {
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class Vehicle {
  - licensePlateNumber: String
  - mileage: Integer
  - type: String
}

class Repair {
  - repairShopName: String
  - repairShopAddress: String
  - employeeWhoTookVehicle: Employee
  - duration: Integer
  - cost: Double
}

class Order {
  - pickupAddress: String
  - deliveryAddress: String
  - comment: String
  - startDate: DateTime
  - endDate: DateTime
  - customer: Customer
  - partnerCompany: PartnerCompany
  - planner: Planner
  - driver: Driver
  - vehicle: Vehicle
}

Employee "1" -- "0..*" Planner
Employee "1" -- "0..*" AdministrativeStaff
Employee "1" -- "0..*" Driver

Customer "1" -- "0..*" Order
PartnerCompany "1" -- "0..*" Order

Vehicle "1" -- "0..*" Repair
Driver "1" -- "0..*" Order
Planner "1" -- "0..*" Order
Order "1" -- "1" Vehicle
Order "1" -- "1" Customer
Order "1" -- "1" Planner
Order "1" -- "1" Driver
@enduml

### Explanation of Key Relationships:

- **Employee** is a base class with subtypes **Planner**, **AdministrativeStaff**, and **Driver**.
- Each **Order** is assigned to one **Driver**, one **Vehicle**, and one **Planner**.
- An **Order** belongs to a **Customer** or a **PartnerCompany**.
- A **Vehicle** may have multiple **Repairs** associated with it.
- Each **Repair** is linked to an **Employee** who took the vehicle for repairs.

